      "text": [
        " - «إِنَّمَا أَكْرَهُ اَلنَّظَرَ إِلَى عَوْرَةِ اَلْمُسْلِمِ فَأَمَّا اَلنَّظَرُ إِلَى عَوْرَةِ مَنْ لَيْسَ بِمُسْلِمٍ مِثْلُ اَلنَّظَرِ إِلَى عَوْرَةِ اَلْحِمَارِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.236 - On the authority of Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) that He said:\n\"Indeed, looking at the private parts of a Muslim is disliked, and looking at the private parts of a non-Muslim is like looking at the private parts of a donkey.\""
        ]
      }
